The paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) falling under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed model uses neural networks and attention mechanisms, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also involves a sentiment-aspect reconstruction procedure, which can be seen as a form of feature engineering or representation learning (cs.NE). Finally, the model uses capsule networks, which are a type of neural network architecture commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), but have also been applied to NLP tasks.
